<i> Timing and Subtitles by the Is it raining yet? Team @ Viki</i>

2
00:00:35.470 --> 00:00:39.300
<i> I heard that if stories fade away by sunlight, they become history </i>

3
00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:44.570
<i> if they are lit by moonlight, they become legends </i>

4
00:00:44.570 --> 00:00:48.890
<i>our story will become a legend. </i>

5
00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:54.890
<i>Bride of the Water God 
 2017</i>

6
00:00:54.890 --> 00:00:58.280
<i>Episode 15</i>

7
00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:10.060
You know, this is supposed to be really romantic.

8
00:01:10.060 --> 00:01:13.550
But, why do I keep thinking about that?

9
00:01:13.550 --> 00:01:14.880
What is?

10
00:01:14.880 --> 00:01:17.850
The seafood kalguksu <i>(chopped noodle soup)</i> I told you about earlier.

11
00:01:17.850 --> 00:01:24.060
To ruin this mood, I keep on remembering that there were 12 short-necked clams in that kalguksu.

12
00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:29.460
Even at the noodle restaurant, my mom and dad kept on fighting.

13
00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:33.940
I was counting the clams in the noodle soup because I was nervous.

14
00:01:33.940 --> 00:01:37.980
There were 12 of them. They were many.

15
00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:41.040
Oh, there are 12 clams.

16
00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:43.240
I need to say this.

17
00:01:43.240 --> 00:01:46.760
But Mom kept on getting mad at Dad.

18
00:01:46.760 --> 00:01:50.120
Mom would ask "what's so important?"

19
00:01:50.120 --> 00:01:53.270
Dad wouldn't say a word and just sat there.

20
00:01:53.270 --> 00:01:58.320
That made Mom even angrier so she would say all types of things.

21
00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:01.810
I was counting the clams over and over again.

22
00:02:01.810 --> 00:02:05.020
No matter how many times I've counted, there were 12 clams.

23
00:02:09.160 --> 00:02:12.170
What exactly was so important

24
00:02:13.350 --> 00:02:16.940
for my dad?

25
00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:20.140
<i> You said you're a god </i>

26
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:22.740
<i> Grant me one wish.. </i>

27
00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:25.420
<i> Let me meet my dad. </i>

28
00:02:25.420 --> 00:02:28.680
<i>I would like to ask him, why he left all these burdens to me,</i>

29
00:02:28.680 --> 00:02:30.330
<i>and if he was able to sleep</i>

30
00:02:30.330 --> 00:02:32.430
<i>or eat just fine?</i>

31
00:02:32.430 --> 00:02:34.100
<i>Tell him to at least take everything away from me now.</i>

32
00:02:34.100 --> 00:02:40.070
<i>He can't even save his own daughter but how can he save the world? If I could ask that one question,</i>

33
00:02:40.820 --> 00:02:43.450
<i>I wouldn't have any other wish.</i>

34
00:02:43.450 --> 00:02:45.190
You never tried to look for him?

35
00:02:45.190 --> 00:02:46.820
I didn't.

36
00:02:46.820 --> 00:02:50.400
What if I found him but he was in Korea?

37
00:02:51.340 --> 00:02:55.390
Suppose he was in Korea all along but he didn't come back to us.

38
00:02:56.390 --> 00:02:58.610
What should I do then?

39
00:02:58.610 --> 00:03:00.620
How about now?

40
00:03:02.970 --> 00:03:05.020
Is that your real wish?

41
00:03:05.020 --> 00:03:09.050
To meet your dad and say whatever is on your mind?

42
00:03:14.030 --> 00:03:16.120
I think so.

43
00:04:01.290 --> 00:04:03.080
What is it?

44
00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:04.590
Just because.

45
00:04:11.580 --> 00:04:14.420
It's nice. This.

46
00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:15.900
What is?

47
00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:18.820
Do you know why people get married?

48
00:04:18.820 --> 00:04:22.450
Because they don't want to part after spending the whole day together.

49
00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:26.260
However, since we live together, that we don't have to do that.

50
00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:29.180
It's nice. Living together.

51
00:04:30.170 --> 00:04:32.550
Is there marriage in the gods' realm too?

52
00:04:32.550 --> 00:04:35.890
You could say there is and there isn't.

53
00:04:35.890 --> 00:04:37.860
What do you mean?

54
00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:42.950
You could get married if you wanted, but exclusivity doesn't apply and it's not binding.

55
00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:44.010
What?

56
00:04:44.010 --> 00:04:48.490
Then, you could cheat anytime you want?

57
00:04:48.490 --> 00:04:52.020
It's very freewheeling.

58
00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:54.660
That's why Lady Yoo Hwa's mom is uncertain.

59
00:04:54.660 --> 00:04:58.520
So who exactly is this Lady Yoo Hwa?

60
00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:00.530
Your daughter.

61
00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:05.230
Joo Mong's mom, King Yoo Ri's maternal grandmother. Since you are King Yoo Ri's maternal grandfather, she's your wife.

62
00:05:05.230 --> 00:05:07.560
I told you I am single.

63
00:05:07.560 --> 00:05:10.680
Ha! It's pointless pretending to be unmarried.

64
00:05:23.380 --> 00:05:25.420
It seems like you're sulking.

65
00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:26.820
What?

66
00:05:26.820 --> 00:05:29.150
Give me a glass of water please.

67
00:05:31.800 --> 00:05:34.800
Seriously, why would law and institutions exist?

68
00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:38.410
Legal authority and binding force, those are all sources of power.

69
00:05:38.410 --> 00:05:42.140
What? Freewheeling? It's not as if this was the animal kingdom.

70
00:05:42.140 --> 00:05:45.420
Is it because they are Natural Men and Women?

71
00:05:45.420 --> 00:05:46.790
Oh?

72
00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:06.060
By chance, is something like polygamy allowed in the gods' realm?

73
00:06:06.060 --> 00:06:07.530
How did you know?

74
00:06:07.530 --> 00:06:10.360
There are goddesses who have many husbands.

75
00:06:10.360 --> 00:06:12.000
Really?

76
00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:13.370
Of course.

77
00:06:13.370 --> 00:06:18.930
They don't age nor die. How could they devote themselves to one man or one woman for such a long time?

78
00:06:18.930 --> 00:06:20.930
Why?

79
00:06:20.930 --> 00:06:23.370
Then you,

80
00:06:23.370 --> 00:06:26.360
how many times were you married?

81
00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:27.640
I told you I have never been married.

82
00:06:27.640 --> 00:06:29.090
Then, who is Lady Yoo Hwa?

83
00:06:29.090 --> 00:06:32.530
Woman, get your act together.

84
00:06:32.530 --> 00:06:34.930
Please give me another glass of water.

85
00:06:45.470 --> 00:06:47.420
One more.

86
00:07:42.300 --> 00:07:44.030
Look here,

87
00:07:44.030 --> 00:07:46.770
what are you plotting?

88
00:07:46.770 --> 00:07:50.050
Can't you tell? I am trying to stay here longer, since I don't want to go upstairs to sleep.

89
00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:51.490
What?

90
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:58.420
If you stay, if you don't leave, what are you planning to do?

91
00:07:58.420 --> 00:08:02.790
Nam Soo Ri isn't coming home tonight because of a part-time job.

92
00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:05.660
Just happens.

93
00:08:06.380 --> 00:08:08.050
S-so?

94
00:08:08.050 --> 00:08:09.890
So...

95
00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:16.070
you and I...

96
00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:24.880
let's watch TV.

97
00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:25.790
TV?

98
00:08:25.790 --> 00:08:27.610
Sit down.

99
00:08:40.630 --> 00:08:42.830
- Yoon So Ah. 
 - Yes?

100
00:08:52.900 --> 00:08:54.660
Seriously.

101
00:08:59.020 --> 00:09:00.980
What did you see to act like this?

102
00:09:00.980 --> 00:09:03.200
Something called a diary?

103
00:09:03.200 --> 00:09:05.500
What did you say?

104
00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:07.570
I don't offer my lap to anyone to lie on.

105
00:09:07.570 --> 00:09:09.130
Why did you read my diary?

106
00:09:09.130 --> 00:09:12.970
Did you't write it so I could read it? 20 years ago at that.

107
00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:13.920
What?

108
00:09:13.920 --> 00:09:16.870
Like you said, I found a poem you wrote when you were just a child.

109
00:09:16.870 --> 00:09:19.360
Title, "Father's Lap".

110
00:09:19.360 --> 00:09:21.070
"Father's lap is mine.

111
00:09:21.070 --> 00:09:25.180
"Yoo Sang Yoo, get out. Yoo Sang Yoo, I curse you."

112
00:09:25.180 --> 00:09:26.880
Do you call that a poem?

113
00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:30.760
You said you were pretty good at writing poems when you were a kid.

114
00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:40.320
There is a rerun for "Male Gods' Dinner".
<i>(a TV-show with good-looking chefs)</i>

115
00:09:40.320 --> 00:09:43.730
Oh, you're being too obvious.

116
00:09:44.500 --> 00:09:48.190
If I had such a great talent like yours,

117
00:09:48.190 --> 00:09:52.440
I will be in charge of cooking until I had to leave.

118
00:10:01.490 --> 00:10:03.630
When are you leaving?

119
00:10:03.630 --> 00:10:06.120
The messenger will come.

120
00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:10.070
It could be tomorrow for all we know.

121
00:10:13.840 --> 00:10:17.560
I guess we are on a day-to-day basis. Like a terminal patient.

122
00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:21.600
When I was an intern,

123
00:10:21.600 --> 00:10:27.330
whenever I had to meet terminal patients or their family members,

124
00:10:27.330 --> 00:10:31.430
I would feel guilty for some reason.

125
00:10:31.430 --> 00:10:35.590
How would I be able to understand how they really feel?

126
00:10:35.590 --> 00:10:40.130
I would comfort them with this and that, as I'd been taught and trained,

127
00:10:40.130 --> 00:10:45.690
but to be honest, I couldn't even begin to fathom how they felt.

128
00:10:45.690 --> 00:10:49.030
Crying with them would have been more valuable than all those words

129
00:10:49.030 --> 00:10:52.630
that would often fall unaccounted.

130
00:10:52.630 --> 00:10:57.230
But I think I still learned something.

131
00:10:57.230 --> 00:11:00.930
How they prepared to say their farewell,

132
00:11:01.700 --> 00:11:04.820
the things left behind after the farewell.

133
00:11:06.140 --> 00:11:10.660
For the families left behind or for me now,

134
00:11:10.660 --> 00:11:15.630
people find a reason to live on without withering away.

135
00:11:16.330 --> 00:11:18.880
The wandering mind will

136
00:11:19.770 --> 00:11:23.660
find a place to stay.

137
00:11:31.020 --> 00:11:33.570
Can I ask you a question?

138
00:11:36.180 --> 00:11:38.330
How about you?

139
00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:43.750
How will you live?

140
00:11:44.990 --> 00:11:51.710
I will only live for 40 to 50 more years, but there is no end for you.

141
00:11:56.030 --> 00:12:01.180
Is it alright for me to desire you?

142
00:12:03.540 --> 00:12:07.980
As long as it's possible, for a long long time,

143
00:12:09.560 --> 00:12:12.640
to live without forgetting me.

144
00:13:26.980 --> 00:13:29.340
What are you doing?

145
00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:31.540
You're awake?

146
00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:36.180
I was up early and I had nothing to do. So I watched the rerun of Male Gods' Dinner.

147
00:13:37.990 --> 00:13:39.770
So?

148
00:13:42.490 --> 00:13:44.240
So?

149
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:46.080
Wait.

150
00:13:48.220 --> 00:13:51.360
Are you making breakfast for me?

151
00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:54.200
So you're the sort of guy who makes breakfast, the type that I've only heard about.

152
00:13:54.200 --> 00:13:55.930
It's because I am hungry.

153
00:13:55.930 --> 00:13:57.820
Really?

154
00:13:57.820 --> 00:14:02.550
Then, I will go back to sleep.

155
00:14:03.620 --> 00:14:06.360
I usually skip breakfast.

156
00:14:06.360 --> 00:14:07.580
Sit right there.

157
00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:11.680
If I have breakfast, I don't feel good.

158
00:14:12.730 --> 00:14:15.050
Just sit.

159
00:14:16.440 --> 00:14:21.000
I will brush my teeth, wash my face and sit at the breakfast table with reverence.

160
00:14:31.930 --> 00:14:37.020
He's cute but I can't tell him he's cute. I think he will get really angry.

161
00:14:38.230 --> 00:14:42.870
Should I give it a try? What if I change into a water lily?

162
00:15:06.750 --> 00:15:10.110
It's breakfast but this is a feast.

163
00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:12.400
Who will eat it all?

164
00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:15.490
Do you know how much food waste pollutes the environment—

165
00:15:15.490 --> 00:15:19.060
If it's to your liking, just say you like it. Simple.

166
00:15:21.880 --> 00:15:23.430
Sit.

167
00:15:30.870 --> 00:15:32.600
Let's eat.

168
00:15:35.860 --> 00:15:37.770
I said eat.

169
00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:40.440
This is how it feels

170
00:15:42.400 --> 00:15:44.220
to have a meal prepared for you.

171
00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:56.930
Eat.

172
00:15:59.990 --> 00:16:02.020
Let's eat.

173
00:16:06.620 --> 00:16:10.710
I locked the door, but there was no potted plant <i>(to hide the keys under)</i> .

174
00:16:27.090 --> 00:16:29.400
He came here to give me the keys. Since there was no potted plant.

175
00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:33.400
I worried about it quite a bit. It didn't seem like you would be going to the clinic for a while.

176
00:16:33.400 --> 00:16:37.260
Should I send it by quick messenger, mail, or call you over to come get it?

177
00:16:37.260 --> 00:16:38.270
Who are you calling over?

178
00:16:38.270 --> 00:16:42.530
That's right. That's why I came myself.

179
00:16:42.530 --> 00:16:44.160
Ah, then at least have a cup of tea...

180
00:16:44.160 --> 00:16:45.340
Who drinks tea first thing in the morning?

181
00:16:45.340 --> 00:16:47.330
There's no law saying I can't have tea first thing in the morning.

182
00:16:47.330 --> 00:16:50.800
In my home, there is such a thing.

183
00:16:50.800 --> 00:16:53.890
You can't drink tea in the morning in my home.

184
00:16:53.890 --> 00:16:55.910
In my house we have breakfast.

185
00:16:55.910 --> 00:16:58.870
If you haven't eaten, eat before you go.

186
00:16:58.870 --> 00:17:01.330
CEO Sin is a really busy person so...

187
00:17:01.330 --> 00:17:04.210
If it's okay, I'll have a little bit.

188
00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:13.330
Wow, Yoon So Ah has great cooking skills.

189
00:17:13.330 --> 00:17:17.630
I did it. This woman didn't lift a finger.

190
00:17:17.630 --> 00:17:19.790
I did it all.

191
00:17:19.790 --> 00:17:21.920
Ah, is that so?

192
00:17:21.920 --> 00:17:26.690
You must not know but this woman has the worst cooking skills.

193
00:17:26.690 --> 00:17:30.950
She also falls asleep wherever. If she just lays down her head, she's out like a light.

194
00:17:30.950 --> 00:17:35.400
So, I always carry her in my arms

195
00:17:35.400 --> 00:17:41.510
and lay her in her bed. I do that. It's really bothersome.

196
00:17:41.510 --> 00:17:44.820
Is that the only thing? She doesn't know how to turn on her porch light

197
00:17:44.820 --> 00:17:47.030
so I always turn it on for her.

198
00:17:47.030 --> 00:17:50.750
She doesn't clean very often so I do that for her.

199
00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:54.980
I bathe every morning

200
00:17:54.980 --> 00:18:01.300
and unsuitably she's very embarrassed at the sight of an undressed male god's body.

201
00:18:01.300 --> 00:18:03.070
Hey.

202
00:18:04.010 --> 00:18:06.100
Am I wrong?

203
00:18:06.100 --> 00:18:08.400
You said that no matter how much you see it, you don't get used to it, right?

204
00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:10.090
Hey.

205
00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:11.710
Was I wrong?

206
00:18:11.710 --> 00:18:16.680
Ah, did you say that you never get tired of seeing it?

207
00:18:19.470 --> 00:18:20.960
Let's eat.

208
00:18:21.880 --> 00:18:26.280
Since you live together, you know a lot about her.

209
00:18:28.890 --> 00:18:33.990
Ah right, Yoon So Ah. I'm  your clinic's new landlord.

210
00:18:33.990 --> 00:18:37.550
Oh! Really?

211
00:18:37.550 --> 00:18:39.850
Are you for real?

212
00:18:39.850 --> 00:18:43.370
Is that why you reduced my rent and security deposit?

213
00:18:43.370 --> 00:18:45.670
I told you, didn't I?

214
00:18:45.670 --> 00:18:50.900
That I would just buy your building. That I have lots of money.

215
00:18:50.900 --> 00:18:53.180
Landlord.

216
00:18:53.180 --> 00:18:57.770
Thank you so much. I really owe you so much.

217
00:18:57.770 --> 00:19:04.370
No, I did that for all the tenants in <i>my</i> building.

218
00:19:04.370 --> 00:19:08.870
Because Chairman Sin has been too greedy of late, they seem to have suffered a lot.

219
00:19:08.870 --> 00:19:10.840
Thank you so much.

220
00:19:10.840 --> 00:19:12.320
I really feel secure now.

221
00:19:12.320 --> 00:19:13.850
It's nothing.

222
00:19:13.850 --> 00:19:18.720
I should become a good landlord.

223
00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:20.630
CEO Sin will definitely be a good landlord...

224
00:19:20.630 --> 00:19:22.980
I am a king!

225
00:19:25.970 --> 00:19:31.260
I'm saying that I'm a king.

226
00:19:39.450 --> 00:19:41.680
That traces of the passage of time in this house look really nice.

227
00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:46.650
I was born in this house, although half of it is now owned by the banks.

228
00:19:54.220 --> 00:19:58.840
<i>It's okay, it's okay,</i>

229
00:19:58.840 --> 00:20:00.840
<i>stay still.</i>

230
00:20:02.480 --> 00:20:06.390
- Yoon So Ah. Did we really never meet before?

231
00:20:06.390 --> 00:20:09.770
Oh, we didn't, at least as far as I remember.

232
00:20:09.770 --> 00:20:11.690
Then why do I keep...

233
00:20:11.690 --> 00:20:14.490
What nonsense are you spouting?

234
00:20:23.220 --> 00:20:24.470
Why don't you sit?

235
00:20:24.470 --> 00:20:28.280
Drinking tea after a meal is a law in my house.

236
00:20:31.610 --> 00:20:33.620
Bring us some tea please.

237
00:20:35.770 --> 00:20:40.350
What is this clumsy "head of the household" sense he's trying to give?

238
00:20:46.200 --> 00:20:49.040
That looks so foreign.

239
00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:53.420
A god who is the king of the Water Kingdom and a half-god half-human.

240
00:21:07.270 --> 00:21:10.660
Why did he change his clothes?

241
00:21:10.660 --> 00:21:12.580
Give it to me in my cup.

242
00:21:13.960 --> 00:21:16.550
I have my own personal cup. It's called Yong Yong.

243
00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:20.500
It's a very artistic cup depicting the good relationship between the owner and his servant.

244
00:21:20.500 --> 00:21:24.950
I bought it for this woman after I did that thing called a "part-time job".

245
00:21:24.950 --> 00:21:26.740
Give it to me in my cup.

246
00:21:27.890 --> 00:21:31.680
Why don't you just drink it in this cup for today?

247
00:21:33.360 --> 00:21:36.390
If you wish, I'll do as you say.

248
00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:42.030
I'm going to go do the dishes.

249
00:21:44.610 --> 00:21:46.540
You look good together.

250
00:21:47.270 --> 00:21:50.910
If you know that then why did you come? Keys?

251
00:21:50.910 --> 00:21:53.450
Did you think I'd blink an eye at your childish provocation?

252
00:21:53.450 --> 00:21:57.820
Even if I'm no match, I can find some loop-holes if I keep poking.

253
00:21:57.820 --> 00:22:01.430
I already told you that the thing that I'm best at is waiting.

254
00:22:01.430 --> 00:22:06.470
Throughout your life, you'll realize how seriously futile your waiting is.

255
00:22:06.470 --> 00:22:10.710
And you'll feel like this life is a failure.

256
00:22:11.570 --> 00:22:14.100
I'm envious of your confidence.

257
00:22:14.880 --> 00:22:17.020
I'm a king.

258
00:22:17.890 --> 00:22:21.250
Yoon So Ah told me that I needn't feel intimidated by things like birth origin.

259
00:22:21.250 --> 00:22:26.510
- She was just saying it.
